I want to bring to the court's attention that the true emissions of the company were disclosed by another source just five weeks after my involvement. While I understand that my attempt at concealing the truth was ultimately futile, I firmly believe that my guilty plea demonstrates my recognition of the severity of my actions. By pleading guilty, I hope to save the court's time and resources and to show my willingness to accept the consequences for my wrongdoing.

I deeply regret my poor decision and the harm caused by my involvement in this incident. It was never my intention to contribute to the company's dishonesty. I understand the importance of transparency and responsibility in the public sphere, particularly when it comes to environmental issues.

To rectify the situation, I have taken immediate steps to distance myself from the company and have returned the bribe money. I am fully committed to making amends for my actions and ensuring that justice is served.

Throughout my involvement in this case, there has been no evidence or record of any prior criminal convictions. I have always strived to be a law-abiding citizen, and this incident is an anomaly in my otherwise upstanding character. My guilty plea demonstrates my remorse and acceptance of responsibility. I kindly ask the court to consider this as a significant mitigating factor.

In light of these circumstances, I humbly request the court's leniency and ask for a fair and just sentence that takes into account my sincere remorse, my guilty plea, and my commitment to making amends.

Thank you for your attention.

